race.comment: BLOCKER TIGER (1) was strongly fancied on the back of a win two starts back but finished second last time (19.14) at this track. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from five starts. Good form should continue. KALINA PEARL (2) skirted wide from an outside draw last start and found the front, leading throughout to win (19.10) at this track in a Grade 5 over 350m. Ran the fastest time on the program in her latest win. One of main contenders. SHE'S A LADETTE (5) boasts a strong record this journey here with four wins and two minors from eight tries. Comes off a (19.31) win last time, scoring by 4 lengths in a Grade 5 over 350m at this track. Among the main chances. Something for the Multiples: HIGH FIVE LAD (6)
